    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.12: \"Electron microscopic localization of a8 immunoreactivity in dendrites in the hilus of the dentate gyrus\"\n- \"B A higher-magnification micrograph of a dendritic spine showing a8 immunoreactivity associated with the post-synaptic density (arrow) and structures resembling the spine apparatus (arrowhead).\"\n\nFig.13: \"Ultrastructural localization of a8 labeling in dendrites in stratum radiatum of the CA3 region of the hippocampus\n- \"a8 immunoreactivity is shown in a dendritic shaft (D) primarily associated with a density post-synaptic to an unlabeled terminal (LIT). B: Labeling for a8 is found in a spine (arrow) emanating from the shaft of a small dendrite. A second dendritic spine on the same dendrite is apparently unlabeled (open arrow)\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Sprague-Dawley rats (Hilltop Lab. Animals, Inc.) were used in these experiments. \"",
